Middle Russian stoat M. e. aestiva
A moderately sized subspecies with dark, tawny or chestnut summer fur
Similar to M. e. richardsonii, but with a broader skull and more extensive white tips on the limbs
Vancouver Island stoat M. e. anguinae
A large subspecies, with a dark-yellowish brown summer coat, a deep yellow underbelly and a massive skull, it resembles Eurasian stoat subspecies more closely than any other American subspecies.
Western Great Lakes stoat M. e. bangsi
A small subspecies, with a dark brown summer coat, its skull is more lightly built than that of richardsonii.
A small subspecies, it has a very light, straw-brownish or greyish coat, which is short and soft. Light spots, sometimes forming a collar, are present on the neck. It does not turn white in winter.
Queen Charlotte stoat M. e. haidarum

Larger than aestiva, but smaller than stabilis, it is distinguished by the irregular pattern on the dividing line between dark and pale fur on the flanks, though 13.5% of Irish stoats exhibit the more typical straight dividing line.
East Siberian stoat M. e. kaneii

A moderately sized subspecies, it is smaller than M. e. tobolica, with close similarities to M. e. arctica. The colour of the summer coat is relatively light, with varying intensities of browning-yellow tinges.

data: Thundarr, Princess Ariel, and Ookla escort a man who is carrying a magical black pearl that can protect anyone from Gemini to Manhattan's ruins while evading the two-faced wizard Gemini and his Groundlings (a race of mutated rat people)

The evil wizard Mindok lost his body in the Great Cataclysm 2000 years earlier, although his brain lived on. He, General Zoa, and Zoa's minions seek out cryogeneticly frozen 20th-century scientists called "Ice People" in a plot to build Mindok a new body to house his brain.
The evil wizard Morag and his raiders attack a cruise ship village to kidnap its inhabitants and steal their life essence.

Thundarr, Princess Ariel, and Ookla come to the aid of the Mok Chieftain Oblach. The trouble is that Captain Kordon: Queen of the River Pirates is after the Mok's hidden treasure and she intends to use the "fire lances" of the ancients to get it.

Thundarr, Princess Ariel, and Ookla are caught up in a battle between wizards who seek to claim the Helmet of Power. Thundarr ends up having to side with the wizard Sholow when he threatens a group of villagers.
A spaceship containing an alien vampire lands on Earth. The alien ends up capturing Princess Ariel and some villagers as a source of food.

The evil wizard Kublai seeks the Golden Scepter of the Yantzee (the only item which can strip him of his magic) and terrorizes the villagers of San Francisco's Chinatown in the process. When Thundarr thwarts his initial attempts, the wizard recruits another barbarian named Zogar to engage him in battle while Kublai tries again to find the scepter.

Noah died 950 years old (3189–2239). Sarai 47, Abram 57, Terah 127, Serug 186, Reu 218, Eber 282, Shelah 312, Arpachshad 347, Shem 447.

Reu died 239 years old (32 + 207) (2457–2218). Abram 78, Terah 148, Serug 207, Eber 303, Shelah 333, Arpachshad 368, Shem 568 years old.

Isaac born. Ishmael 14, Sarah 90, Abraham 100, Terah 170, Serug 229, Eber 325, Shelah 355, Arpachshad 390, Shem 490 years old.
Serug died 230 years old (2425-2195). Isaac 1 year old, Ishmael 15, Sarah 91, Abraham 101, Terah 171, Eber 326, Shelah 356, Arpachshad 391, Shem 491 years old.
Terah died 205 years old (2366–2161). Isaac 25, Ishmael 49, Sarah 125, Abraham 135, Eber 320, Shelah 390, Arpachshad 425, Shem 525 years old.

Sarah died 127 years old (2286–2159) at Hebron. Abraham then purchased from Ephron the Hittite the field with the cave in it, in Machpelah east of Mamre, for 400 shekels of silver as a burying place. Isaac 27, Ishmael 51, Abraham 137, Eber 322, Shelah 392, Arpachshad 427, Shem 527 years old.
Arpachshad died 438 years old (35 + 403) (2586–2148). Isaac 48, Ishmael 62, Sarah 138, Abraham 148, Eber 373, Shelah 403, Shem 538 years old.
Shem died 600 years old (2686–2086). Esau and Jacob 50, Isaac 110, Ishmael 124, Eber 435 years old.
Ishmael died 137 years old (2210–2073). Esau and Jacob 63, Isaac 123, Eber 448 years old.
Jacob sent away to Paddan-aram to Laban. Jacob 77, Esau 77, Isaac 137, Eber 462 years old. Jacob begins to serve Laban 7 years for Rachel (2059–2052).
Genesis 28:5 Genesis 30:25-36 Genesis 31:36-41 Genesis 37:2 Genesis 40:23-41:1 Genesis 41:46-53 Genesis 47:9 Genesis 47:28
Eber died 464 years old (34 + 430) (2521–2057). Jacob 79, Esau 79, Isaac 139 years old.

Jacob completed 7 years service to Laban for Rachel (2059–2052), was given Leah instead. Jacob 86, Esau 86, Isaac 146 years old. Rachel given to Jacob in return for another 7 years service (2052–2045).
Levi born (about 27–30 months after Jacob married Leah).
Joseph born. Jacob 91, Esau 91, Isaac 151 years old. Jacob began to serve Laban another 6 years for his flocks (2045–2039)
Genesis 30:25-32 Genesis 31:41 Genesis 37:2 Genesis 40:23-41:1 Genesis 47:9 Genesis 47:28

God commanded Jacob to return to the land of his fathers and to his kindred. Jacob departed. Laban pursued, confronted Jacob, made covenant at Mizpah, departed. Jacob called Israel. Esau met Jacob, departed. Joseph 6, Jacob/Israel 97, Esau 97, Isaac 157 years old.
Joseph 17 years old was sold, taken into Egypt. Jacob/Israel 108, Isaac 168 years old.
Joseph 28 years old, in prison interpreted the dreams of Pharaoh's chief butler and chief baker. The chief butler forgets Joseph for 2 whole years (2017–2015).
Isaac died 180 years old (2196–2016). Joseph 29, Jacob 120 years old.

Joseph 30 years old brought out of prison, interpreted Pharaoh's dreams, entered Pharaoh's service, was placed over the whole land of Egypt, and married to Asenath. The 7 years of plenty began (2015–2008). Jacob/Israel 121 years old.
Manasseh and Ephraim born before the year of famine came. Joseph 36, Israel 127 years old.
The 7 years of famine began. Joseph 37, Israel 128 years old.

Israel entered Egypt. Joseph settled his father and his brothers, giving them a possession in the land of Rameses. Joseph 39, Israel 130 years old. 5 remaining years of famine followed (2006–2001). Israel dwelt there 17 years (2006–1989). The people of Israel dwelt in the land of Egypt 430 years (2006–1576).
Israel died 147 years old (2136–1989). Joseph 56 years old (2044–1988.

30 years after Israel entered Egypt, the Egyptians began to enslave the people of Israel. Abraham's posterity would be aliens in a land belonging to others, who would enslave them and ill-treat them 400 years (1976–1576). Joseph 69 years old (2045–1976).
Joseph died 110 years old (2045–1935). Hyksos ruled Egypt 500 years 2200–1700 BC.

Levi died 137 years old (c. 2050–1913). The people of Israel had continued in Egypt about 93 years after Israel had entered Egypt (2006 to c. 1913) and about 22 years after Joseph died (1935to c. 1913).
Aaron born. The people of Israel had continued in Egypt 276 years after Joseph died (1935–1659) (1976–1659) and had been enslaved 317 years (1976–1659).
Exodus 7:7 Exodus 12:40-41 Numbers 33:39 Joshua 14:7 Joshua 14:10 Joshua 24:29
Exodus 2:1-4 Exodus 7:7 Numbers 20:1 Numbers 33:38-39 Deuteronomy 34:7 Joshua 14:7
Joshua born. Moses 42, Aaron 45 years old.
Exodus 7:7 Exodus 12:40-41 Numbers 33:38-39 Deuteronomy 2:14 Deuteronomy 34:7 Joshua 14:7 Joshua 14:10 Joshua 24:29

From the wilderness of Paran Moses sent Hoshea/Joshua the son of Nun and 11 other men from all the tribes of Israel to spy out the land of Canaan. Only Caleb and Joshua brought up a good report, the others an evil report. The congregation cried out, wishing they had died in Egypt or in the wilderness. God then declared according to the number of days in which they spied out the land, 40 days, for every day a year, the people would wander in the wilderness until the wicked congregation 20 years old and upward died. Joshua 40, Moses 82, Aaron 85 years old. Joshua states plainly that he and the brethren who went up with him to spy out the land were sent from Kadesh-barnea, not the wilderness of Paran. Moses states plainly and explicitly that the time from their leaving Kadesh-barnea until the entire generation, the men of war, had perished was 38 years, "as the LORD had sworn to them." (1574–1536)
Numbers 13:2 Numbers 11:35-14:2 Numbers 14:26-38 Numbers 20:1 Deuteronomy 2:14-15 Joshua 14:7-8
The 40th year after the people of Israel had come out of the land of Egypt (1576–1536) Aaron died 123 years old (1659–1536). Moses died 120 years old (1656–1536). Joshua 78 years old.

Joshua died 110 years old (1614–1504). "They buried him..." (Joshua 24:30) "And Israel served the LORD all the days of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua and had known all the work which the LORD did for Israel." (Joshua 24:31) A plain, explicit number representing the remaining days of life of the elders who outlived Joshua cannot be drawn from the text of the Bible; the Bible does not tell the period of time elapsed between the burial of Joshua and the day when "all that generation also were gathered to their fathers."
Exodus 7:7 Exodus 12:40-41 Numbers 33:38-39 Deuteronomy 34:7 Joshua 14:7-10 Joshua 24:29-31 Judges 2:8-10

"...the people served the LORD...all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua...and there arose a generation after them, who did not know the LORD or the work which he had done for Israel." A plain, explicit meaning for the exact period of "the days of the elders" and of the "generation after them" cannot be drawn from the text of the Bible; the Bible does not tell the number of days of that generation. "...whenever the judge died, they turned back and behaved worse than their fathers..." (Judges 2:18-19)
Othniel, son of Kenaz the younger brother of Caleb, judged Israel, and the land had rest for 40 years, then Othniel died. The ages of Othniel and Kenaz are not given in the Bible.
Israel served Eglon king of Moab 18 years.
Ehud delivered Israel and the land had rest for 80 years.
After Ehud died, Shamgar delivered Israel.
Jabin king of Canaan cruelly oppressed the people of Israel for 20 years. At that time Deborah was judging Israel.
The land of Israel had rest 80 years.
Israel in the hand of Midian 7 years.
The land had rest 40 years in the days of Gideon.
Eli born (1173 BC). Elon judged Israel 10 years.
Israel in the hand of the Philistines 40 years (20 years 1155–1135 before Samson judged in the days of the Philistines 1135–1115 BC.)
Samson judged Israel 20 years in the days of the Philistines.
Eli 58 years old (1173–1115) judged Israel 40 years (1115–1075).
The ark of the covenant captured by the Philistines. Eli died 98 years old (1173–1075). David 17 years old.
The ark of the covenant sent back to Israel, remained in the house of Abinadab 20 years at Kiriath-jearim (1075–1055).

Samuel judged Israel 11 years after Eli died (1075–1064). He made his sons judges, he anointed Saul king, and when Saul was rejected he anointed David king. David slew Goliath, entered Saul's service. Samuel died (1064). Saul seeks to kill David.
David fled Saul and dwelt in the land of the Philistines at Ziklag 1 year 4 months.
Saul slain on Mount Gilboa. David departed Ziklag, went to Hebron. David 30 years old (1092–1062).
David 30 years old (1092–1062) anointed king over house of Judah (1062), reigned over Judah 7 years 6 months (1062–1055).

David anointed king over Israel by all the elders of Judah, took Jerusalem, brought the ark of the covenant up to Jerusalem from the house of Abinadab at Kiriath-jearim where it had been kept 20 years (1075–1055), then placed it in the house of Obed-edom 3 months. David 37 years old.
David reigned over all Israel and Judah 33 years.
David died 70 years old (30 + 40) (1092–1022). Solomon sat upon the throne of David, reigned 40 years (1022–982). Rehoboam born (1022).

Solomon began to build the house of the LORD the 4th year of his reign (1022–1018). According to the literal meaning of the biblical text, from the end of the reign of Zedekiah and the burning of the temple, back to the 4th year of the reign of Solomon, the total of the years of the reigns of the kings of Judah (shown in this table from 2 Chronicles through 1 Kings) is 431 years (587 to 1018). According to 1 Kings 6:1 the 4th year of Solomon (1018) was the 480th year after the people of Israel came out of the land of Egypt, giving the date of the Exodus as 1498 (1498–1018). The sum of the years plainly stated in the Bible from the 4th year of Solomon back to the Exodus (shown in this table, from Numbers through 2 Chronicles) is 558 years, giving the date of the Exodus as 1576 (1576–1018). This is a difference of 78 years (558 years and 480 years).
Solomon finished building the house of the LORD the 11th year of his reign (1022–1011). He was 7 years building it (1018–1011).
Solomon died (age not given), he had reigned 40 years (1022–982). Rehoboam began to reign. Jeroboam then returned and began to reign some time after him over the kingdom of Israel.
Rehoboam reigned 17 years (982-965), he died 58 years old (41 + 17) (1022–964) the 18th year of the reign of Jeroboam, who had begun his own reign some time after the beginning of Rehoboam's reign.
Jehoshaphat reigned 25 years, he died 60 years old (35 + 25).
Jehoram/Joram reigned 8 years, he died 40 years old (32 + 8).
Ahaziah reigned 1 year, he died 23 years old (22 + 1), and he died 43 years old (42 + 1).
Jehoash/Joash reigned 40 years, he died 47 years old (7 + 40).
Amaziah reigned 29 years, he died 54 years old (25 + 29).
Azariah/Uzziah reigned 52 years, he died 68 years old (16 + 42).
Jotham reigned 16 years, he died 41 years old (25 + 16).
Ahaz reigned 16 years, he died 36 years old (20 + 16).
Hezekiah reigned 29 years, he died 54 years old (25 + 29).
Manasseh reigned 55 years, he died 67 years old (12 + 55)
Amon reigned 2 years, he died 24 years old (22 + 2)
Josiah reigned 31 years, he died 39 years old (8 + 31)
Jehoahaz reigned 3 months, and Pharaoh Neco took him away.
Eliakim/Jehoiakim reigned 11 years, he died 36 years old (25 + 11). He was bound in fetters to take him to Babylon.
Jehoiachin reigned 3 months and ten days, and was carried away to Babylon 18 years old. He was 8 years old.
Mattaniah/Zedekiah 21 years old (598) reigned 11 years, until he was 32 years old (587).
Jerusalem falls, Zedekiah 32 years old blinded and taken to Babylon, the Temple is burned, the people taken into exile. The 19th year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar.

Nebuchadnezzar II reigned 605–562 BCE, succeeded by his son Awel-marduk. "Babylon", Daniel C. Browning, Holman Illustrated Bible Dictionary, pp. 155-160, "Evil-merodach", p. 521. Jehoiachin freed from prison 37th year of his exile to Babylon (598–561), the first year of the reign of Evil-Merodach/Awel-marduk (reigned 561–560)

Beginning of 2nd year of the coming to the the house of God at Jerusalem, the builders laid the foundation of the Temple of the LORD. Ezra 3:8-11. The people of the land discouraged them, made the Jews afraid, brought accusations against them. Work on the house of God ceased (18 years, 538–520). Ezra 4:4-5, 24.
3rd year of Cyrus king of Persia, Daniel's vision of man in linen who revealed what was to befall his people in the latter days. Daniel 10-12.

2nd year of Darius the king (520), Jews resumed rebuilding the house of God with support of prophets Haggai and Zechariah. Ezra 5:1-2. 29 August 520, 2nd year, 6th month, 1st day of the month, Haggai's 1st message. Haggai 1:1-11. 21 September 520, 2nd year, 6th month, 24th day of the month, Temple building resumed. Haggai 1:12-15 17 October 520, 2nd year, 7th month, 21st day of the month, Haggai's 2nd message. Haggai 2:1-9 October-November 520, 2nd year, 8th month, Zechariah's ministry began. Zechariah 1:1-6. 18 December 520, 2nd year, 9th month, 24th day of the month, Haggai's 3rd and 4th messages. Haggai 2:10-23 15 February 519, 2nd year, 11th month, 24th day of the month, Zechariah's night visions. Zechariah 1:7-6:8. Zechariah was a leading priest at time of Joiakim's high priesthood, possibly the same as the prophet. Nehemiah 12:16 "Haggai, book of", Holman Illustrated Bible Dictionary, p. 701, "Zechariah 18." p. 1701, "Zechariah, book of", p. 1702. Literally, "the going forth of the word of the LORD to restore and rebuild Jerusalem" (Daniel 9:24-27) was announced by Zechariah in Jerusalem in the 2nd year, 11th month, 24th day of the month: "Cry out: Thus says the LORD of hosts...I have returned to Jerusalem with compassion...the measuring line shall be stretched out over Jerusalem. Cry again: Thus says the LORD of hosts: My cities shall again overflow with prosperity, and the LORD will again comfort Zion and again choose Jerusalem." Zechariah 1:14-17. 70 weeks of years = 490 years, from 519 to 29 BCE.

2nd year of the reign of "Artaxerxes the Great" (484) Mordecai's dream. Mordecai overheard the plot of eunuchs Gabatha and Tharra to kill Artaxerxes, reported it, Haman son of Hammedatha in great honor with the king, sought injury to Mordecai and his people because of the eunuchs. Esther 11:2-12:6. 3rd year of the reign of Ahasuerus (483), Vashti deposed, beautiful young virgins sought, Esther taken, made queen. Esther 1:1-3, 12-21; 2:1-4, 8, 16-17.

7th year of Ahasuerus (479, reigned 486–465/4 BCE) Ezra went up from Babylon, journeyed from the 1st month to the 5th month, to Jerusalem, and at his word, from the 9th month to the 1st month (479–478), the Jews separated themselves from the people of the land and put away their foreign wives with their children.

12th year of Ahasuerus the "pur" ("lot", plural purim, "lots") cast before Haman in the 1st month, and an edict issued in the king's name to annihilate all the Jews on the 14th day of the 12th month (473). Haman exposed, executed, Mordecai given his position, issued decree authorizing Jews to defend themselves, they smote their enemies, days of Purim fixed.

"...and in the days of Artaxerxes..." (reigned 465–424) Bishlam, Mithredath and Tabeel, and Rehum and Shimshai wrote to Artaxerxes king of Persia, he sent answer to them to make a decree that the men rebuilding the wall and the city of Jerusalem cease, they went in haste and by force and power made them cease.

20th year of Artaxerxes, Hananiah came to Susa, told Nehemiah, cup-bearer to the king, that the wall of Jerusalem was broken down and the gates burned with fire. Nehemiah obtained a decree that Jerusalem be rebuilt, went to Jerusalem, inspected the wall. Nehemiah 1:1-2:15. According to Daniel 9:25, 490 years from the decree of Artaxerxes through Nehemiah to the governors of province Beyond the River is (445 + 45) from 445 BCE to 45 CE/A.D. 45. The wall was rebuilt in 52 days and finished in the 7th month, 1st day. Nehemiah 6:15. The people were enrolled by genealogies, 1 in 10 volunteered to live in Jerusalem. The 7th month Ezra read the Law before the Water Gate, an assembly of 42,360 persons besides 7,337 servants. Nehemiah 7:5, 66-67; 8:1-2. The 24th day of the 7th month the Israelites separated themselves from all foreigners. Nehemiah 9:1-2. Nehemiah the governor gave his brother Hanani and Hananiah the governor of the cattle charge over Jerusalem. Nehemiah 7:2.
Nehemiah 1:1-2:15 Nehemiah 6:15 Nehemiah 7:2-5 Nehemiah 7:73-8:1 Nehemiah 7:66-67 Nehemiah 8:1-2 Nehemiah 9:1-2 Nehemiah 12:27-45 Nehemiah 13:1-3

20th year of Artaxerxes to the 32nd year (12 years) Nehemiah was governor of Judah. Nehemiah returned to Artaxerxes in the 32nd year of Artaxerxes. After some time (date not stated in the Bible) he received leave to return to Jerusalem, cleansed the Temple.

High priests recorded in Book of Nehemiah 12:10-11: Jeshua, father of Joiakim (c. 586–537 BCE) Ezra 2:2, 36, 40 Joiakim, father of Eliashib (c. 510 BCE) Nehemiah 12:10, 12, 26 Eliashib, father of Joiada, Nehemiah 3:1, 20; 12:10; 13:28; Ezra 10:6 Joiada, father of Jonathan (c. 425 BCE) Nehemiah 12:10-11, 22; 13:28 Jonathan, father of Jaddua, Nehemiah 12:11, 14 (425–333 is 92 years) "Jeshua 3.", Holman Illustrated Bible Dictionary, p. 898-899, "Joiakim", p. 940, "Eliashib 3." p. 477, "Joiada 2." p. 940b, "Jonathan 11. 12." p. 944

Jaddua, son of Jonathan, high priest probably at the end of the Persian period when Alexander the Great approached Jerusalem about 333 BCE. Nehemiah 12:11, 22. "Jaddua", Holman Illustrated Bible Dictionary, p. 864b.

table-1600-289.caption: Season 2 (1981–1982)
data: The wizard Skullus and his soldiers are enslaving villagers living in a ruined oil refinery and using them to attack the fortress of his enemy, the wizard Octagon.

After being defeated by Thundarr, the evil wizard Sarott stumbles into a research lab that holds the miniaturized City of Thieves. Its ruler Vortak promises Sarott a free rein to use the city's advanced army to enslave humans and other wizards if he can restore it to normal size. To do so, he'll need the Gauntlet of Power which can boost his magic to enlarge the city.

The trio investigate a sector called the Mystery Zone where several ships get wrecked on an island. They learn the evil witch Circe is responsible as she needs a young sorceress to overcome a curse in which she will turn to stone if she leaves the island. When Ariel arrives with Thundarr and Ookla, Circe gets her opportunity as she switches bodies with her and becomes a threat to the others as she tries to leave the island.

Thundarr, Princess Ariel, and Ookla battle the evil wizard Vashtarr when he steals the Crystal of Prophecy that can give the details of his downfall. When it shatters in his efforts to retrieve it, the prophecy is foretold as they learn three women will unite to defeat him. One is Maya, an element-shifter buried in the ruins of the old city of Endorr. Another is Cinda, a hermitic barbarian living in the Canyon of Death whose staff grants her great strength. The last is Valerie Storm, a fashion model from Old Earth who is abducted and taken prisoner by Vashtarr himself.

During a battle with Yando (a supposed wizard with unusual magic), Thundarr is struck by red negative lightning which significantly diminishes the power of his Sunsword. The weapon can be restored at the nearby Pool of Power, but it is stolen by Yando who seeks to have the Sunsword's power for himself.

Thundarr's friend Thorac is accused of stealing a village's fuel and is about to receive a death sentence (by being boiled alive over a geyser) when the barbarian rescues him. Thorac is granted a reprieve when Thundarr and the group investigate the crime, eventually learning the town's sheriff Korb is in league with the evil wizard Artemus. Artemus had stolen the fuel to power his Death Ship and gain the approval of the Council of Wizards.
